    <description>Plants 0.5–1 cm, occasionally taller. Leaves 2–3.5 mm, crisped when dry, narrowly
        lanceolate, gradually tapering to an acute apex, margins serrulate with small teeth
        distally, distal cells subquadrate, 10–14 µm wide, often wider than long, somewhat
        incrassate. Seta 2–4.5 mm. Capsule 0.7–1 mm; peristome teeth linear to linear-lanceolate,
        broadened at base, smooth to striolate, perforate or irregular. Spores 15–21
        µm.</description>
    <phenology>Capsules mature summer.</phenology>
